org.diirt.graphene.profile.utils

Class StopWatch

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.diirt.graphene.profile.utils.StopWatch
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Settings

    public class StopWatch
extends Object
implements Settings
    A timing system to track a set of durations of a process. Useful in profiling where the stop watch starts counting at the beginning of a process, stops counting at the end, and then repeats multiple iterations.
    Author:
    carcassi, asbarber

    • Constructor Detail

      • StopWatch

        public StopWatch(int maxAttempts)
        Constructs and initializes the watch from the max number of times the watch will be stopped. The watch cannot stop more than the number of maxAttempts.
        Parameters:
        maxAttempts - max number of times that will be tracked

    • Method Detail

      • start

        public void start()
        Starts the watch. The watch should not start more than the max number of attempts set in the constructor.

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Stops the watch. The watch should not stop more than the max number of attempts set in the constructor. This is NOT verified in the method call as to improve efficiency.

      • getNanoAverages

        public ListLong getNanoAverages(int start)
        Gets the average of all sets of timings after the first start timings. Inclusive of timings[start] and inclusive of timings[MAX]. Example: timings = [5 10 15 20 25] start = 2 timings[start] = 15 averages[0] = 15 / 1 averages[1] = (15 + 20) / 2 averages[2] = (15 + 20 + 25) / 2
        Parameters:
        start - starting index of timings
        Returns:
        the set of averages of timings

        Returns:
